response: Over a period of 2 to 3 years, follow a sample of 50 volunteers. Throughout this time period, they will be sometimes be asked to record their thoughts in a journal while your cousin acts as a researcher but is actually performing his/her supposed mind reading. Compare what your cousin reports to what the participant wrote and see how accurate the reading was. Other times throughout this time period, they will be asked to come into the lab and will be made aware of the mind reading while they are writing their thoughts. The accuracy results from the sessions where subjects knew vs. didn't know their mind was being read will be compared.
